casebody.data:
MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

00-1913. State ex rel. Ohio Patrolmen’s Benevolent Assn. v. Medina Cty. Sheriff.

In Mandamus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus.

Upon consideration of the joint application for dismissal,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the application for dismissal be, and hereby is, granted.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
